  "text": "We present two validation studies of the statistical properties derived in Section II, a simulation study and a study performed on a physical phantom with a real system. The Monte Carlo simulations test our findings under the assumptions of a scattering medium generated by a Gaussian random process. The purpose of the simulation study is to verify that: 1) the mean and autocovariance functions in [CITATION_1] and (21) accurately predict sample estimates of the quantities and 2) the coherence term in (14) (or S36) is indeed relatively small and may often be neglected. The physical phantom is used to check how well the RF autocovariance function can be used to predict the intensity PS using (23). ",
